  "prompt": "Why is Quora blocking my name saying it doesn't conform?",
  "response": "Quora has specific guidelines and policies regarding usernames and display names to maintain a respectful and safe environment for its users. If Quora is blocking your name, it might be due to one or more of the following reasons:\n\n1. **Inappropriate Content**: Your name may contain offensive, vulgar, or inappropriate language.\n2. **Impersonation**: If your name resembles that of a well-known person or public figure, Quora might restrict it to prevent impersonation.\n3. **Symbols and Formatting**: Quora typically does not allow certain symbols, numbers, or excessive punctuation in names.\n4. **Length**: The name may not meet the platform's length requirements (too short or too long).\n5. **Spammy Connotations**: If your name appears to be spammy or promotional in nature, it may be blocked.\n6. **Policy Violations**: It might violate other specific Quora naming policies or guidelines.\n\nTo resolve this issue, you might want to try using a different name that complies with Quora's guidelines. If you're unsure, you can refer to Quora's help center or community guidelines for more information.",
